@startuml Sequence - Tenant-Landlord Messaging
!theme plain

actor Tenant
actor Landlord
participant "Chat Screen" as App
participant "ChatRepository" as ChatRepo
participant "MessageRepository" as MsgRepo
participant "AnalyticsRepository" as Analytics
participant "Firestore" as DB

Tenant -> App: Initiate chat
activate App

App -> ChatRepo: getOrCreateChat(listingId, tenantId, landlordId)
activate ChatRepo
ChatRepo -> DB: Query chats collection
DB --> ChatRepo: Existing chat or null

alt Chat exists
    ChatRepo --> ChatRepo: Return existing chatId
else Chat doesn't exist
    ChatRepo -> DB: Create new chat document
    DB --> ChatRepo: Return new chatId
end
deactivate ChatRepo

Tenant -> App: Type message
activate App

Tenant -> App: Send message

App -> MsgRepo: saveMessage(chatId, text, senderId)
activate MsgRepo
MsgRepo -> DB: Add document to messages subcollection
DB --> MsgRepo: success
deactivate MsgRepo

App -> Analytics: logListingMessage()
activate Analytics
Analytics -> DB: Write LISTING_MESSAGE event
DB --> Analytics: success
deactivate Analytics

App --> Tenant: Show message in chat
deactivate App

== Real-time update ==

Landlord -> App: Chat screen open
activate App

App -> MsgRepo: subscribeToMessages(chatId)
activate MsgRepo
MsgRepo -> DB: Attach listener
DB --> App: Emit message updates
deactivate MsgRepo

App --> Landlord: Display new message from Tenant
deactivate App

@enduml